Selling my Finnish M39 Mosin Nagant in 7.62x54r. It is a 1943 SAKO manufacture on a hex receiver with a wartime production stock (This is not a SKY-Civil Guard rifle). It is a formerly issued rifle but in good condition. Stock has dings all over but no wood chunks missing or anything. Bluing is worn but no rust and the bore is still very good. Cosmoline has been cleaned and I keep this rifle clean. It is in perfect working order and has been checked for headspacing. I acquired it recently and shot about 150 rounds through it. I really like the rifle but am willing to part with it since it is not a very practical rifle for me and I can't shoot it as often as I originally intended to. This thing is really meant for outdoor shooting beyond 100 yards :)

postcontent:
I am selling my H&K VP9. First off, this is an amazing pistol! I have never had a more comfortable and secure grip which shows in your tight shot groups. The pistol is in mint condition. The pistol comes with everything that is in the pictures. Pistol, two H&K magazines, different grips for customization, H&K hard case and user manual.  
Description:
The VP9 was developed by Heckler & Koch to meet the need for a safe, robust, ergonomically enhanced, striker fired handgun.
Easily identify whether the firing pin is in the cocked or uncocked mode. Quickly view the amount of ammunition present. With slide releases present on both sides of the frame and a magazine release on the rear, bottom portion of the trigger guard, VP9 controls are completely ambidextrous.
The VP9’s high strength polymer frame includes a unique ergonomic handgun grip design consisting of interchangeable grip panels and backstraps, as well as a dustcover with a standard Picatinny rail interface. Molded finger grooves in the front of the pistol’s grip also instinctively position an operator’s hand for optimal shooting.
The barrel — made from canon grade steel — ensures long service life.  The polygonal bore profile, with no traditional lands-and-grooves rifling, contributes to longer service life as well as a slight increase in muzzle velocity.
The VP9 trigger surpasses those found on competitors. It has a short, light take-up with a solid, single action type break followed by a short positive reset.
The extended Picatinny MIL-STD-1913 rail molded into the VP9’s polymer frame can mount a wide variety of lights, laser aimers, and other accessories. The rail has been tested and certified to handle mounted accessories up to 5.6 ounces.
